The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Saturday, July 05, 2003 				Metro Recommends
				 																THE FILM				 																																	(British  Council, July 7, 7 pm) Supriyo Sens personal film about  Partition has won the BBC Audience Award for Best Documentary  at the 2nd Commonwealth Film Festival in Manchester. Catch  its screening, with Mrinal Sen (picture above) as chief guest.  THE LAUNCH				 																																	(Nandan  2, July 8, 6 pm) An evening for Pete Seeger fans  a video  message from the legendary folk singer; Suchitra Mitra to  release Seegers book We Shall Overcome and 200  other songs; screening of video documentaries Where  have all the flowers gone and We Shall Overcome.  Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee is chief guest at the function.  THE CD				 																																	(Gareth  Gates) Crescendo Music has launched an Express Yourself contest  in town to promote the pop star. The best instinct expressed  will be awarded with a chance to join Gates birthday bash  and his live concert in Thailand. The Gates gang needs to  log into contestsouthernspicemusic.com.  THE BOOK				 																																	(Edited  by Benedict Allen) This anthology of worlds revealed by explorers  brings to life what it feels like to walk off the edge of  the known world and to emerge dazed, dying, yet triumphant.  Through those who have set off into the unknown and returned  to bring the unknown back to their people. 

